<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.AA/6–2946: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-03T20:00:00-04:00">July 3,
                                    1946—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>113. Bevin told <gloss target="#t_SEC1">SEC</gloss> Paris July 3 that
                            Brit Govt expects to inform Ireland that Brit will support its candidacy
                            for UN membership.</p>
                        <p>Since Brit are approaching Irish, and in view of De Valera’s<note n="99" xml:id="d213fn99">Eamon De Valera, Prime Minister of Eire.</note>
                            probable negative attitude (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>s 70,
                            June 26[<hi rend="italic">27</hi>] and 72 June 29),<note n="1" xml:id="d213fn1">Neither printed.</note> we have decided not (repeat
                            not) to make any approach to Irish at this time. Please inform us of
                            Irish reaction to British approach.<note n="2" xml:id="d213fn2">Repeated
                                to New York as telegram 129.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>